bilingual.source: So she went to the market place.
The bank is next to the market.
The museum is next to the market.
I decided to drive to the market.
I'm going to buy some at the market.
Many market places are full of entertainers.
bilingual.target: 许多市场充满了表演者。

list.abstract: market（英 [ˈmɑːkɪt]，美 [ˈmɑːrkɪt]），英语单词，作名词为集市；市场；股票市场。作动词为市场宣传；市场推广；推销。短语搭配有job market（人才市场）。例句为“Oh, here is one on Market Street.（哦，交易大街上有一家。）” market相关近义词有exchanges、store等。

yingyinNormal.en: What is that? That's America's housing market.
yingyinNormal.zh: 什么事？倒塌的正是美国房地产市场。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, another market to expand to balding gay men.
yingyinNormal.zh: 噢，又一个可以开拓的市场，裸体基佬。

yingyinNormal.en: This market is getting busy now, but it is nothing compared to Beijing's biggest wholesale food market.
yingyinNormal.zh: 现在市场已经繁忙起来，但跟北京最大的食品批发市场相比，这可真不值一提。

yingyinNormal.en: I need to talk to my wife. This market won't last.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我还得跟我太太商量商量。市场不会一直这样的。

yingyinNormal.en: No, no, no, no. No stocks. I want to short the housing market.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不，不是股票，我想要做空房地产市场。

yingyinNormal.en: So, demo it to the consumer. And market the components separately.
yingyinNormal.zh: 所以，把它展示给客户，作为部件推向市场。

yingyinNormal.en: Follow the scent of frankincense and herbs to the city's spice market.
yingyinNormal.zh: 跟随乳香和草药的香气，就可以找到香料市场。

yingyinNormal.en: If someone's trying to hijack the market, shouldn't we head to the trading floor?
yingyinNormal.zh: 要有人想操纵市场，我们不该去交易大厅吗？

yingyinNormal.en: You bought your sheets at a flea market? Ross come on, you gotta loosen the purse strings a little.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你上旧货市场买床单？罗斯，别这么小器吧。

yingyinNormal.en: Tonight, the stock market will close at 10,233 points, after regaining 617 points.
yingyinNormal.zh: 今晚，证券市场会于10,233点收市，上涨617点。

yingyinNormal.en: So, what can I bring you from the market? A rose. Like the one in the painting.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那么，要我从市场给你带点什么过来？一支玫瑰，像画里的那样。

yingyinNormal.en: How much bigger is the market for insuring mortgage bonds than actual mortgages? About 20 times.
yingyinNormal.zh: 担保房贷债券的市场要比实际房贷大多少？大约20倍。

yingyinNormal.en: Camouflaging bald spots. That's primarily a male concern. Perhaps could expand our market.
yingyinNormal.zh: 当作遮羞的用途，这能够吸引男士目光，也许我们可以扩大市场。

yingyinNormal.en: Sue's given us a list of hot pot ingredients to find in the market, lotus root, mushrooms and beef.
yingyinNormal.zh: 苏给了我们一张火锅料单到市场入货，莲藕，蘑菇还有牛肉。

yingyinNormal.en: You need help, little man? Are you lost from the tour? I crashed the stock market yesterday.
yingyinNormal.zh: 需要帮助吗，小家伙？参观迷路了吗？我昨天击溃了你们的证券市场。

yingyinNormal.en: We are in the best market in Beijing and it would be criminal not to cook up a traditional New Year feast.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们在北京最好的市场里面，不烹传统新年大餐，这真是罪过。

yingyinNormal.en: Your seeds were taking over my land. You control over 90% of the market, Ed. You control the food.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你的种子在侵占我的地，你控制着90%的市场，艾德，你控制着食物。

yingyinNormal.en: But these two forces, the social force and the market force are not additive, when one comes the other one goes away.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但这两者，社会和市场推动力不是附加的，两者不同时出现。

yingyinNormal.en: We can meet them at that Mexican place. Ooh, a Mexican place. I forgot about the Latina market!
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们可以去那家墨西哥店找他们啊。墨西哥店那地儿！我居然忘了拉美市场！

yingyinNormal.en: Imagine if all the fresh food consumed by a city was all put together in one place. Well, feast your eyes on this, Fadi Food Market. This is the biggest wholesale markets in Asia.
yingyinNormal.zh: 试想想一个城市需要消耗的所有新鲜食品全部集中在一个地方。那好，享受这个视觉盛宴吧，新发地市场。这是亚洲最大的批发市场。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

sense_info_list.en: an area or arena in which commercial dealings are conducted

examination_example.sentence: Gen Zs are about to hit the streets looking for work in a labor <highlight>market</highlight> that's tighter than it's been in decades.
examination_example.sentence_trans: z世代即将走上街头，在比几十年前更紧张的劳动力市场寻找工作。

examination_example.sentence: CEOs must have a good sense of financial <highlight>markets</highlight> and maybe even how the company should trade in them.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 首席执行官们必须对金融市场有很好的理解，甚至可能对公司应该如何交易金融市场有很好的理解。

examination_example.sentence: With the content of papers secured for free, the publisher needs only find a <highlight>market</highlight> for its journal.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 由于论文内容是免费的，出版商只需要为其期刊找到一个市场。

examination_example.sentence: Such eggs could be <highlight>marketed</highlight> as helping to fight climate change.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这种鸡蛋可以作为有助于应对气候变化的产品进行销售。

sense_info_list.en: buy or sell provisions in a market

word_usage.usage: market作名词，表示“交易；买卖”时，常用单数形式，如：the world market in coffee
market作及物动词，其后可接名词或代词，如：market many types of goods，不可接从句或不定式（to do的形式）。

examination_example.sentence: That the UK lags behind is due to the opposition to taxes and regulation of our aggressively pro-<highlight>market</highlight> ruling party.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 英国之所以落后，是因为我们激进的亲市场执政党反对税收和监管。

examination_example.sentence: The way you pre-sell a movie in a foreign <highlight>market</highlight> is based on relevant talent.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在国外市场预售电影的方式取决于相关人才。

examination_example.sentence: I was reminded of this again recently listening to an interview with Nicole Haddow, explaining how she cracked the property <highlight>market</highlight> at 31.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我最近听了妮可·哈多的采访，描述她如何在31岁时破解了房地产市场，这使我又想起了这件事。

sense_info_list.en: a demand for a particular commodity or service

examination_example.sentence: They overestimate the potential <highlight>market</highlight> of autonomous cars.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们高估了自动驾驶汽车的潜在市场。

examination_example.sentence: Because instead of being real life, it is, for the most part, impression management, a way of <highlight>marketing</highlight> yourself.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 因为在很大程度上，它不是真实的生活，而是印象管理，一种自我营销的方式。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>Marketing</highlight> their products with ordinary ingredients.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 用普通原料推销他们的产品。

sense_info_list.en: buy or sell provisions in a market

examination_example.sentence: There is something almost delightful in the detachment from reality of advertisements showing mass-produced cars <highlight>marketed</highlight> as symbols of individuality and of freedom.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 广告显示大规模生产的汽车作为个性和自由的象征在市场上销售，这种脱离现实的做法几乎令人愉快。

word_usage.usage:
on/in the market表示“出售”，“上市”。
示例：These computers aren’t yet on the market. 
这些计算机还未上市。

examination_example.sentence_trans: 最近，美国市场的自行车数量已经增长到了263,000辆，比去年增长了25%。

examination_example.sentence: We believe expanding such protections would make the labor <highlight>market</highlight> more fair and efficient.

examination_example.sentence: While the continued gender penalty in the labor <highlight>market</highlight> is frustrating, our finding that misperceived weight does not harm workers is more heartening.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 尽管劳动力市场上一直存在的性别歧视令人沮丧，但我们发现，对体重的误判并不会对员工造成伤害，这更为可喜。

examination_example.sentence: On our first morning in Paris, I went around the comer to the food <highlight>market</highlight> to pick up some groceries.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我们在巴黎的第一天早上，我去街角的食品市场买了些杂货。

examination_example.sentence: The <highlight>market</highlight> at the corner of Friendship Street and Xinhua Road has given way to a supermarket.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 友谊街和新华路拐角处的市场已被一家超市取代。

examination_example.sentence: A latest study on the college job <highlight>market</highlight> showed that employers wanted to hire 22% fewer graduates this year than last.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一项关于大学就业市场的最新研究显示，今年雇主想要雇用的毕业生比去年少了22%。

examination_example.sentence: Oh, here is one on <highlight>Market</highlight> Street.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 哦，交易大街上有一家。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>Market</highlight> Nature to Children.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 把自然推销给年轻人。

examination_example.sentence: He documented his journey as he set about treating nature as a brand to be <highlight>marketed</highlight> to young people.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他记录了他的旅程，因为他开始把大自然作为一个品牌，向年轻人推销。
